OL,3,CUltra-processed foods and alcohol
OL,4,Ccontribute to 2.7m deaths a year, says
OL,5,CWHO
OL,7,FUltra-processed foods (UPFs), alcohol,
OL,8,Ftobacco and fossil fuels are killing
OL,9,F2.7 million people every year across
OL,10,FEurope, according to the World Health
OL,11,FOrganisation (WHO).
OL,13,FExperts said "powerful industries" are
OL,14,Fdriving ill health and premature death
OL,15,Fbecause they interfere in government
OL,16,Fpolicies and efforts to cut cases of
OL,17,Fcancer, heart disease and diabetes.
