OL,3,CUltra-processed foods and alcohol
OL,4,Ccontribute to 2.7m deaths a year, says
OL,5,CWHO
OL,7,FIt said: "These commercial products
OL,8,Fcontribute to 24% of all deaths,
OL,9,Fincluding significant mortality from
OL,10,Fcardiovascular diseases (51.4%) and
OL,11,Fcancer (46.4%).
OL,13,F"Overall, tobacco, alcohol, UPF food
OL,14,Fand fuel industries are wholly or
OL,15,Fpartly responsible for 2.7 million
OL,16,Fdeaths per year in Europe, according
OL,17,Fto the document."
