OL,3,CUltra-processed foods and alcohol
OL,4,Ccontribute to 2.7m deaths a year, says
OL,5,CWHO
OL,7,FMeanwhile, the global picture shows
OL,8,Fthat tobacco, UPFs, fossil fuels and
OL,9,Falcohol cause 19 million deaths per
OL,10,Fyear, or 34% of all deaths.
OL,12,FBreaking down the data, WHO said 1.15
OL,13,Fmillion deaths per year in Europe are
OL,14,Fcaused by smoking, 426,857 by alcohol,
OL,15,F117,290 by diets high in processed
OL,16,Fmeats and 252,187 by diets high in
OL,17,Fsalt.
